B d liu tng hp ny c thit k m phng cc loi tnh cch ca con ngi Hng ni, Hng ngoi v c ngi c c hng ngoi ln hng ni da trn nhiu c im hnh vi v tm l khc nhau.

B d liu ny cha 20.000 mc nhp v 30 ct, bao gm 29 c im s biu th cc ch s tnh cch v 1 ct nhn (personality_type).

Trong

  • personality_type: bin mc tiu gm 3 kiu tnh cch: Introvert(hng ni), Extrovert(hng ngoi), or Ambivert (hn hp).

  • social_energy: Xu hng n nhn nng lng t tng tc x hi (010).

  • alone_time_preference: th hin s thoi mi vi s c n.

  • talkativeness: Xu hng tham gia v cc cuc tr chuyn.

  • deep_reflection: Tn sut suy ngh su hoc suy ngh ni tm.

  • group_comfort: D ho nhp vi cc nhm/ hi.

  • party_liking: S thch th i vi cc ba tic v cc s kin.

  • listening_skill: Kh nng lng nghe

  • empathy: kh nng ng cm hay thu hiu cm xc ca ngi khc.

  • creativity: s t duy sng to.

  • organization: Mc u tin cho cc trt t, k hoch.

  • leadership: S thoi mi khi lm lnh o.

  • risk_taking: S chp nhn ri ro.

  • public_speaking_comfort: Mc thoi mi khi ni chuyn trc m ng hoc cng chng.

  • curiosity: Mc thch hc tp v khm ph nhng ci mi.

  • routine_preference: Th hin thi quen v s t pht.

  • excitement_seeking: Mc mong mun nhng tri nghim mi m.

  • friendliness: Mc thn thin.

  • emotional_stability: Kh nng kim sot v cn bng khi cng thng.

  • planning: Xu hng lp k hoch t trc.

  • spontaneity: Hnh ng t pht khng c k hoch t trc.

  • adventurousness: Sn sng th nhng hot ng mi v mo him.

  • reading_habit: Tn sut c sch bo.

  • sports_interest: Mc quan tm ti th thao hoc cc hot ng th cht.

  • online_social_usage: Thi gian dnh cho mng x hi.

  • travel_desire: S thch du lch v khm ph nhng a im mi.

  • gadget_usage: Tn sut s dng cc thit b cng ngh v tin ch.

  • work_style_collaborative: mc lm vic nhm so vi vi vic lm c nhn.

  • decision_speed: Thi gian a ra cc quyt nh.

  • stress_handling: Kh nng qun l cng thng cch hiu qu.

Nhn xt: B d liu khng c gi tr no b thiu.

Ta ly cc ct bin thc hin PCA (tr bin personality_type) 

numeric_data <- data[, -1]

V boxplot

boxplot(numeric_data, main = "Boxplot Before Outlier Removal", las = 2, col = "skyblue")

Nhn xt: Ta nhn thy c cc gi tr ngoi lai mt s bin.

Kim tra gi tr ngoi lai v tin hnh x l

V y l b d liu nhiu chiu nn khng th s dng IQR xc nh cc gi tr ngoi lai m cn s dng khong cch Mahalanobis xc nh cc gi tr ngoi lai.

mahalanobis_distance <- mahalanobis(numeric_data, colMeans(numeric_data), cov(numeric_data))
cutoff_value <- qchisq(0.95, df = ncol(numeric_data)) # 95% quantile for chi-square distribution
outliers <- which(mahalanobis_distance > cutoff_value)

In s lng ngoi lai v tnh t l ngoi lai trong b d liu

cat("s lng ngoi lai:", length(outliers), "\n")
## s lng ngoi lai: 821
cat("T l ngoi lai:", length(outliers)/nrow(data)*100, "%", "\n")
## T l ngoi lai: 4.105 %

Nhn xt: c 821 gi tr ngoi lai chim 4,105% gi tr quan trc b d liu. V s lng ngoi lai khng ln nn ta tin hnh loi b cc gi tr ny.

Loi b cc gi tr ngoi lai.

data_no_outliers <- numeric_data[-outliers, ]

V li boxplot sau khi loi b cc gi tr ngoi lai

boxplot(data_no_outliers, main = "Boxplot After Outlier Removal", las = 2, col = "skyblue")

Nhn xt: mc d c th thy vn cn nhiu gi tr ngoi lai, nhng c th nhn thy cc c trng ca b d liu

Kim tra li b d liu sau khi loi b gi tr ngoi lai

Nhn xt:

  • Theo nguyn tc Kaiser, nn gi li 3 thnh phn chnh (PC1, PC2, PC3), v ch cc thnh phn ny c tr ring ln hn 1.

  • Ba thnh phn chnh u tin tho nguyn tc Kaiser t l phng sai ng gp l 48,596%

  • Ta thy t thnh phn chnh th nht (PC1) chim 41,62% t l phng sai, chim phn ln bin ng

  • Nhng t thnh phn chnh th 2 tr i th t l ng gp phng sai gim mnh ch cn di 4%. Ta c th suy on t thnh phn chnh th 2 s c cc ng gp vo phng sai ca b d liu l rt nh. Da vo t l ng gp phng sai c th nhn 2 thnh phn chnh l PC1 v PC2 b qua nguyn tc Kaiser

# Scree plot
# Custom scree plot using ggplot2
pca_variance <- data.frame(
  PC = 1:length(pca_result$sdev),
  Variance = pca_result$sdev^2 / sum(pca_result$sdev^2) * 100
)
p3 <- ggplot(pca_variance, aes(x = PC, y = Variance)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  labs(title = "Scree Plot", x = "Principal Components", y = "Percentage of Variance Explained (%)") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size = 14))

# Display scree plot
print(p3)

Nhn xt:

  • PC1: Gii thch khong 40% phng sai.

  • PC2 t tr i: Gim mnh xung di mc 4% phng sai, th bt u thoi ra. Ph hp vi nhn nh trn l ch nn gi li 2 thnh phn chnh l PC1 v PC2.

  • im elbow c th xc nh l im PC2.

# Loading plot for PC1 and PC2 with arrows
pca_loadings <- as.data.frame(pca_result$rotation[, 1:2]) # Extract loadings for PC1 and PC2

# Scale loadings for better visualization (optional, adjust multiplier as needed)

pca_loadings$PC2 <- pca_loadings$PC2 * 5

p4 <- ggplot() +
  geom_segment(data = pca_loadings, aes(x = 0, y = 0, xend = PC1, yend = PC2), 
               arrow = arrow(length = unit(0.2, "cm")), color = "red") +
  geom_text(data = pca_loadings, aes(x = PC1, y = PC2, label = variable), 
            vjust = 1.5, hjust = 0.5, size = 3, color = "red") +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, linetype = "dashed", color = "gray") +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = "dashed", color = "gray") +
  labs(title = "Loading Plot with Arrows (PC1 vs PC2)", x = "PC1 Loadings", y = "PC2 Loadings") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size = 14)) +
  xlim(-1, 1) + ylim(-1, 1) # Adjust limits based on scaled loadings

# Display loading plot
print(p4)

t bin ni bt pha m, nhng mt s nh decision_speed c th c ti nh m.

ngha: PC1 ch yu phn bit hng ni (introversion) v hng ngoi (extraversion), trong khi PC2 lin quan n kh nng cm xc, t chc, v t m. iu ny ph hp vi ma trn ti trc.
